cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM. 

The paper presents a model for generating image captions, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The model is based on deep learning techniques, specifically recurrent neural networks and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also applies the model to retrieval tasks, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
